{
  "title": "A Dynamic Extension of the Period Life Table",
  "abstract": "The standard period life table is based entirely on the death probabilities of the given period. Popular (not expert) usage of life expectancies from a period table typically ignores the fact that the expectancies make no allowance for future declines",
